Spot Gold Drops 0.5% to $1,418.80 an Ounce; Silver Declines

-- B y   K y o u n g w h a   K i m
-- 
2011-03-15T02:44:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/spot-gold-drops-0-5-to-1-418-80-per-ounce-falls-for-first-day-in-three.html
Gold for immediate delivery
declined 0.5 percent to $1,418.80 an ounce at 10:41 a.m. in  Singapore  today. Cash silver weakend 0.7 percent to $35.68 an
ounce, while palladium and platinum also fell 0.9 percent to
$739.75 and $1,738.88 respectively.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kyoungwha Kim at 
 kkim19@bloomberg.net  